Is there anything wrong with the way I'm swapping the nodes here? Also, how should I handle the deletion of the old root if the rotation changes the root of the entire tree?

I'm getting a StackOverflowError when trying to insert a large number of sorted elements into my AVL tree. This is strange because AVL trees are supposed to stay balanced, so the depth should be logarithmic. I suspect my rotation logic is not actually balancing the tree, causing it to degenerate into a linked list. Here is my insertion balance check:

if (balance > 1) {
    if (key < root.left.key) return rotateRight(root);
    else {
        root.left = rotateLeft(root.left);
        return rotateRight(root);
