I'm implementing an AVL tree in Java for a school project, and I'm running into an issue where my tree isn't actually balancing after a series of insertions. I've implemented the rotation logic, but the tree remains skewed. I suspect the issue is in how I'm updating the heights of the nodes after a rotation. For example, when I insert 10, 20, and 30, it stays as a linked list instead of rotating 20 to the root. Here is my rotation code:

private Node rotateRight(Node y) {
